<br>
There really is no reason 2 raids can't take place per day. It would just require a little common courtesy on the part of both raid leaders working out what times they both will go up and everyone will be happy and have a great time. <br>
<br>
The Planes aren't quite like the rest of the zones in that MOBs respawn after 15-30 minutes each and you can't very well enter a Plane and move to an area and pull to that location as long as you like. The planes are designed and laid out in such a way that you port up, slowly work your way through and leave. A few hours later, the MOBs begin respawning.<br>
<br>
Again though, it can and should be worked out for maximum enjoyment of the planes. If anything we can thank Verant for setting it up this way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualaoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alaoan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Legionairre</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/01 6:15:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why dont people do this...</span><hr size=1> Respawn on Fear is 13 hours. It really won't work having multiple raids on the same day.  In an ideal world where no one gets wiped out, everyone shows up to raids on time, and you have the proper class balance it might be a bit easier to work out.  But we all know this isn't an ideal world (To much LDing)<br>
